  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "アーリとカーバンクルが家に帰る手助けをしよう！出会うすべての奇妙なキャラクターに挑戦し、ぷよぷよの難しいゲームをクリアして、土地を進み、安全な場所に戻ろう。ぷよを消し、連鎖コンボを作り、相手のプレイフィールドを埋めるための狂った競争が繰り広げられる、スピーディーなパズルゲームです。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Puyo Pop, known as Minna de Puyo Puyo (みんなでぷよぷよ; \"Everybody Puyo Puyo\") in Japan, is the first of the Puyo Puyo games made for the Game Boy Advance, and the first produced by Sonic Team. It is the last game to solely use the original Madō Monogatari cast, as later games would introduce many new characters to go alongside them.\nThe Japanese title refers to the game's four player mode and became a staple in future games. The Western title is simply named Puyo Pop (a recycled title from the Neo-Geo Pocket version of Puyo Puyo 2).",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
